## Example

```jsx
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    console.log("Count is:", count);
  }, [count]);

  return (
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
      Increment
    </button>
  );
}
```

Every time `count` changes, `useEffect` runs.

